<title>USA: First Midwest Bancorp sets oddlot offer.</title>
<headline>First Midwest Bancorp sets oddlot offer.</headline>
<dateline>ITASCA, Ill. 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Midwest Bancorp Inc said it established a program under which shareholders owning less than 100 shares may sell their holdings to the company at the highest closing price of its common stock without brokerage costs during the effective dates of the program.</p>
<p>The program will run April 1 through April 30.</p>
<p>First Midwest is a bank holding company with $3.1 billion in assets.</p>
